## Quick Start

### 1. Clone and Setup

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd {{ project_name }}
make setup
```

### 2. Start Development Environment

```bash
make dev
```

This starts all services with hot reload:

| Service | URL |
|---------|-----|
| Frontend | http://localhost:{{ ports.frontend }} |
| Backend API | http://localhost:{{ ports.backend }}/api/v1 |
| API Docs (Swagger) | http://localhost:{{ ports.backend }}/docs |
| MongoDB | localhost:{{ ports.mongodb }} |
| Redis | localhost:{{ ports.redis }} |
{% if auth_required %}
| KeyCloak Admin | http://localhost:{{ ports.keycloak }} |
{% endif %}

### 3. Seed Data (Optional)

```bash
make seed
```

## Development

### Available Commands

```bash
make help          # Show all available commands
make dev           # Start development environment
make test-all      # Run all tests
make test-backend  # Run backend tests only
make test-frontend # Run frontend unit tests only
make test-e2e      # Run Playwright E2E tests
make lint-all      # Lint all code
make format-all    # Format all code
make clean         # Remove containers and build artifacts
make logs          # Follow service logs
```

